# Workforce Optimization (Constraint-Based Scheduling)

A small, production-structured optimization project that converts demand requirements into a feasible, cost-minimizing staffing plan.

This repo is intentionally designed to demonstrate senior applied data science skills:
- mathematical formulation and constraints
- solver implementation (OR-Tools CP-SAT)
- reproducible project structure + CI

## Quickstart

1) Create venv + install

make install

2) Solve the toy problem

make solve

You should see a schedule and total cost printed in the terminal.

## What’s implemented

- Toy workforce scheduling model (binary assignment)
- Coverage constraints (meet demand per time slot)
- Max shifts per employee
- Objective: minimize total staffing cost
